Rating: 3
The baking time is way off. Based on other readers' experience having the edges done before the middle I lowered the temp to 325 and baked it for an hour; it was perfect. A tester will not come out clean. I used a 9-inch springform pan, heavily buttered, and had no problem with sticking. This is a wonderful cake. Not too pretty (fresh raspberries are essential aesthetics-wise). I used a 3.5 oz. bar of Ghirardelli "Twilight Delight" dark chocolate in the icing and Scharffen Berger cocoa in the cake, and a jar of frozen fruit jam from the Northwest that someone had given me. Though it's not seedless, I really recommend it for this purpose (it could be strained, though I didn't bother); it's not cooked, and has a fabulously vivid raspberry taste that really comes through in this recipe. This is a swell dessert, luxurious but easily made. It doesn't need to be served warm, though it's best that way in my opinion; if you made it ahead it can easily be rewarmed.

