This has the potential to be a good dessert, but the baking directions in my experience were completely wrong. After 30 minutes the middle two thirds of the cake was still very jiggly and a tester was NOT coming out clean. I checked it every 5 minutes and ended up baking it 50 minutes before a tester came out clean. Unfortunately, I should not have done this because the cake ended up being overbaked. SO -bake it 35 minutes, but do NOT expect a tester to come out clean. AND - use a springform pan. It happened to be the only 9 inch round I had and it's a good thing because the cake rose way more than 2 inches! Two other tips - cool the frosting down before pouring it into the pan and DO use dutch process cocoa if you have it.

